"title": "1220: God, as shepherd",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1220: god, as shepherd",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The image of God as a shepherd points to his continual direction, guidance and care for his people.</p>\n<h2>Shepherd as a title for God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps80:1\">PSA 80:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:24\">GEN 49:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl12:11\">ECC 12:11</a></p>\n<h2>God's people are his flock</h2>\n<h3>Israel is God's flock</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:7\">PSA 95:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps79:13\">PSA 79:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps100:3\">PSA 100:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer50:7\">JER 50:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:31\">EZK 34:31</a></p>\n<h3>The church is God's flock</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2\">1PE 5:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:32\">LUK 12:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28-Acts20:29\">ACT 20:28–20:29</a></p>\n<h2>The tasks undertaken by God the shepherd</h2>\n<h3>The shepherd leads and guides</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:2-Ps23:3\">PSA 23:2–23:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:11\">ISA 40:11</a></p>\n<h3>The shepherd provides</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:1\">PSA 23:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:15\">GEN 48:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:5-Ps23:6\">PSA 23:5–23:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos4:16\">HOS 4:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:14\">MIC 7:14</a></p>\n<h3>The shepherd protects</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:9\">PSA 28:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:23-Gen49:24\">GEN 49:23–49:24</a></p>\n<h3>The shepherd saves those who are lost or scattered</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:10\">JER 31:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:176\">PSA 119:176</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:6\">ISA 53:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:11-Ezek34:16\">EZK 34:11–34:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:12-Matt18:14\">MAT 18:12–18:14</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:3-Luke15:7\">LUK 15:3–15:7</a></p>\n<h3>The shepherd judges</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:17-Ezek34:22\">EZK 34:17–34:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:1\">JER 23:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech10:2-Zech10:3\">ZEC 10:2–10:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech11:16\">ZEC 11:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:32-Matt25:46\">MAT 25:32–25:46</a></p>\n<h2>God gives shepherds to be leaders over his people</h2>\n<h3>He gives David's line</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:23\">EZK 34:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:2\">2SA 5:2</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:2\">1CH 11:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:70-Ps78:72\">PSA 78:70–78:72</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:23-Ezek34:24\">EZK 34:23–34:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:24\">EZK 37:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic5:4\">MIC 5:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt2:6\">MAT 2:6</a></p>\n<h3>He gives individual leaders</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:28\">ISA 44:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:11\">ISA 63:11</a></p>\n<h3>He gives faithful leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:15\">JER 3:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:4\">JER 23:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:2-1Pet5:4\">1PE 5:2–5:4</a></p>",
